  "text": "The CSS layout reflow pipeline in Gecko spans three core subsystems: (1) Frame construction: nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp builds the frame tree from DOM nodes via ContentInserted/ContentRemoved. (2) Block layout reflow: nsBlockFrame.cpp is the central file implementing Reflow(), ReflowDirtyLines(), ReflowBlockFrame(), and DoReflowInlineFrames(); it is supported by BlockReflowState.cpp (per-reflow state), nsBlockReflowContext.cpp (child block reflow context), nsLineLayout.cpp (inline-level reflow within lines), ReflowInput.cpp (constraint computation), ReflowOutput.cpp (reflow metrics), and nsContainerFrame.cpp (generic ReflowChild/FinishReflowChild). (3) Dirty-frame invalidation: PresShell::FrameNeedsReflow() (in PresShell.cpp) propagates NS_FRAME_IS_DIRTY / NS_FRAME_HAS_DIRTY_CHILDREN bits up the frame tree and adds dirty roots to mDirtyRoots; ProcessReflowCommands then drives the reflow. nsBlockFrame::MarkLineDirty/MarkLineDirtyForInterrupt handle line-level dirty marking. RestyleManager.cpp bridges style changes to reflow requests. nsIFrame.cpp contains base-class dirty-bit manipulation.",
